title: For Sale:  .223 Lake City 09 Factory New Brass Qty 100
postcontent:
For sale is 1 bag of 100 new Lake City 09 (2009) .223 Remington brass FACTORY NEW.  The price listed is for 1 bag of 100.  

    This brass is true 5.56 x 45 MM mil-spec, heavy duty brass.  This is the same brass in use with the US Military.  As with all brass, cases should be sized, chamfered and de-burred before loading.

    A light "staining" may be found on the case neck of new brass. This is due to annealing. Annealing is a process, performed by the manufacturer, which involves rapid heating to a specified temperature followed by rapid cooling. This process imparts cases with the proper hardness to securely hold a bullet as well as gives flexibility to expand and contract upon firing and repeated forming. The "staining" is a residue from this process. This stain may be removed by tumbling before loading.

title: For Sale/Trade:  M35 beretta 1944
postcontent:
this beretta pistol was included in a delivery of 65,000 Beretta M1934/35 pistols delivered to the German Army Headquarters in Italy between Aug 1944 and Feb, 1945. Those serial # were 534000/599000.
 After the 8 September 1943 armistice between Italy and the Allies, the Germans saddled Beretta with three engineers from Germany. Moreover the factory was GARRISONED BY THE SS! Weapons of that time, even the ones produced for the Germans, bore the punch mark 4UT, (Quarto Ufficio tecnico di Controllo Armi e Munizioni--4th Technnical Control Unit...
-an C. Still, in Axis Pistols, page 107, states,
"It is likely that almost all of the 4/UT, ...were used by the German Army". He also includes two other variations in this statement, "1944 dated and blank slide Model 1935".
Ugo Menchini, in Pietro Beretta Le Automatiche, regarding an M1934, page 255, states,
"In late 1940 there appears an oval including the punch mark IVU. It refers to the 4th technical Control Unit of the FAG, where inspection was carried out."
 Note that, while they seem to represent the same inspectors, the "IVU" is not the same mark as the "4UT". The IVU would be found on the pre RSI model M1934, and the 4UT would be found on the RSI model M1935.
 These are the reasons why I believe that it is likely that all of the 4UT Berettas WERE RSI pistols!! the IVU and the 4UT were the same office, but under Italian management -the IVU, before the surrender of Italy, and German the 4UT, so after september, 8 1943.

pistol is in near unissued condition and a prime example of strain on axis weapons fabrication late in the war, with tooling and machinery marks throughout, it comes with one extra original period magazine.
REDACTED

produced by Theodor Kommer Waffenfabrik GmbH, Zella Mehlis. It is almost an exact copy of the Belgian, FN Browning Model 1910.
  the Kommer Model 4 is not a commonly encountered vintage pistol,German police and civil guard were known to carry as well as some officers.
 production about 1936 and ceased in 1940 with only a small quantity made during this period. A very difficult pistol to locate for ones collection. Right slide is blank. of

you some time so that you don't waste your breath? What you are going to
tell me is that because we are in the firearms manufacturing business 
you no
longer want my business."
"That is correct", he says. I
replied "That is okay, we will move our accounts as soon as possible. We
can find a 2nd Amendment friendly bank that will be glad to have our
 business. You won't mind if I tell the NRA, SCI and everyone one I know

say.

and

title: For Sale/Trade:  P226 Tactical Operations in 9mm W/ TB
postcontent: This post is for a P226 Tactical Operations in 9mm. There areis several modifications that have been made to this  weapon to make it slightly better than its factory original counterparts (IMHO). The first modification that was made to the grips. The factory original magwell grips were stippled to increase their function and enable better grip in adverse conditions (i.e. wet or sweaty hands, bloody hands, etc) The second modification was made to the barrel. I sent my P226 back to the factory to install and fit a Threaded Barrel into the weapon. The third modification was done the same time as the narrel and was the removel of the siglite rear night sight and tru glo front tritium fiber optic combo sight, in favor for trijicon rear and front tritium night sights. I found that after much shooting the fiber optic combo front sights fiber optic would fall out ( apparently its a fairly common occurrence). Lastly this weapon has been factory refinished and will include a blackhawk lvl 3 weapon light duty holster w/ thigh rig, Blackhawk xiphos weaponlight, a galco leather snap holster, and six 20 round magazines.

Made in the USA."
